  <section>
    <div class="flow" style="--flow-space: var(--space-s);">
      <h2 class="heading-l">Status colors</h2>
      <p>Four semantic feedback colors for communicating system state. Use these in callouts, badges, alert icons, and validation messages.</p>

    
      <div class="">
  <div class="cluster gap" style="flex-wrap: wrap;">
    <div class="cluster gap">
      <div style="width: 3rem; height: 3rem; border-radius: 0.25rem; background: var(--color-status-ok);"></div>
      <div><code>--color-status-ok</code><br><span>#1a4</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="cluster gap">
      <div style="width: 3rem; height: 3rem; border-radius: 0.25rem; background: var(--color-status-warning);"></div>
      <div><code>--color-status-warning</code><br><span>#e90</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="cluster gap">
      <div style="width: 3rem; height: 3rem; border-radius: 0.25rem; background: var(--color-status-ko);"></div>
      <div><code>--color-status-ko</code><br><span>#d22</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="cluster gap">
      <div style="width: 3rem; height: 3rem; border-radius: 0.25rem; background: var(--color-status-info);"></div>
      <div><code>--color-status-info</code><br><span>#26e</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
      </div>

      <details class="margin-y-s">
        <summary>Show code</summary>
        <pre class="padding-m"><code>&lt;div class=&quot;cluster gap-s&quot; style=&quot;flex-wrap: wrap;&quot;&gt;
