  <section>
    <div class="flow" style="--flow-space: var(--space-s);">
      <h2 class="heading-l">Brand tokens</h2>
      <p>These two tokens are <strong>required</strong> and must be set by the consuming application before importing the library. The library does not provide defaults for them — components that depend on these tokens will fall back gracefully (e.g. focus rings use <code>#26e</code> as a fallback), but for correct brand-aligned rendering you must supply both.</p>

      <table class="">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Token</th>
            <th>Required</th>
            <th>Description</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--color-brand</code></td>
            <td>Yes</td>
            <td>Primary interactive color. Used for buttons, focus rings, links, and primary actions. Should have at least 4.5:1 contrast against white.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--color-accent</code></td>
            <td>Yes</td>
            <td>Secondary or highlight color. Used for decorative accents, hover states, and secondary actions.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <p>Define them in your application before any Cubito UI import:</p>
      <pre><code>:root {
    --color-brand:  #0057d9;
    --color-accent: #f5a623;
  }</code></pre>
  
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="flow" style="--flow-space: var(--space-s);">
      <h2 class="heading-l">Surface aliases</h2>
      <p>These tokens map to semantic roles and automatically adapt in dark mode. Always use these in component styles — never reference neutral palette tokens directly.</p>

      <table class="">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Token</th><th>Default (light)</th><th>Description</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--color</code></td>
            <td><code>var(--color-black)</code></td>
            <td>Default foreground / text color</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--background</code></td>
            <td><code>var(--color-white)</code></td>
            <td>Default page background</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--link-color</code></td>
            <td><code>inherit</code></td>
            <td>Default link color</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--link-color-hover</code></td>
            <td><code>var(--link-color)</code></td>
            <td>Link color on hover</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--highlight-background</code></td>
            <td><code>color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 15%, transparent)</code></td>
            <td>Mark / highlight background tint</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--highlight-color</code></td>
            <td><code>var(--color)</code></td>
            <td>Mark / highlight foreground color</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
  
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="flow" style="--flow-space: var(--space-s);">
      <h2 class="heading-l">Dark mode</h2>
      <p>All surface alias tokens automatically adapt when the operating system is set to dark mode via <code>prefers-color-scheme: dark</code>. No JavaScript or extra class names are needed. Neutral palette tokens (the raw <code>--color-neutral-*</code> values) do not change — they are fixed reference points. The semantic aliases are what switch.</p>
      <div class="callout wide" data-variant="brand" role="note"><p>To test dark mode locally, toggle the OS appearance setting or use DevTools to emulate <code>prefers-color-scheme: dark</code>.</p></div>
  
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="flow" style="--flow-space: var(--space-s);">
      <h2 class="heading-l">Border and focus tokens</h2>

      <table class="">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Token</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>--border-radius-s</code></td><td><code>0.125rem</code></td><td>Extra-small corner radius</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--border-radius-m</code></td><td><code>0.25rem</code></td><td>Standard corner radius</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--border-radius-l</code></td><td><code>0.5rem</code></td><td>Large corner radius (cards, modals)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--border-radius</code></td><td><code>var(--border-radius-m)</code></td><td>Base alias — override to change all corners globally</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--border-s</code></td><td><code>0.0625rem</code> (~1px)</td><td>Hairline border width</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--border-m</code></td><td><code>0.125rem</code> (~2px)</td><td>Standard border width</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--border-l</code></td><td><code>0.25rem</code> (~4px)</td><td>Thick border width</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--focus-ring-width</code></td><td><code>0.1875rem</code></td><td>Focus outline thickness</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--focus-ring-offset</code></td><td><code>0.125rem</code></td><td>Gap between element and focus ring</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--focus-ring-color</code></td><td><code>var(--color-brand, #26e)</code></td><td>Focus ring color (falls back to <code>#26e</code>)</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
  
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="flow" style="--flow-space: var(--space-s);">
      <h2 class="heading-l">All color tokens</h2>

      <table class="">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Token</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>--color-current</code></td><td><code>currentColor</code></td><td>Alias for <code>currentColor</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--color-white</code></td><td><code>#ffffff</code></td><td>Pure white constant</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--color-black</code></td><td><code>#0a0a0a</code></td><td>Near-black constant</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--color-neutral-50</code></td><td><code>#fcfcfc</code></td><td>Lightest neutral</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--color-neutral-100</code></td><td><code>#f5f5f5</code></td><td></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--color-neutral-200</code></td><td><code>#e2e2e2</code></td><td>Subtle dividers, borders</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--color-neutral-300</code></td><td><code>#c9c9c9</code></td><td>Disabled borders</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--color-neutral-400</code></td><td><code>#999999</code></td><td>Placeholder text</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--color-neutral-500</code></td><td><code>#6d6d6d</code></td><td>Secondary text</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--color-neutral-600</code></td><td><code>#4b4b4b</code></td><td></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--color-neutral-700</code></td><td><code>#333333</code></td><td>Body text on light</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--color-neutral-800</code></td><td><code>#1e1e1e</code></td><td>Dark surface</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--color-neutral-900</code></td><td><code>#121212</code></td><td>Darkest surface</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--color-neutral-950</code></td><td><code>#0a0a0a</code></td><td>Near-black surface</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--color-status-ok</code></td><td><code>#1a4</code></td><td>Success / positive state</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--color-status-warning</code></td><td><code>#e90</code></td><td>Warning / caution state</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--color-status-ko</code></td><td><code>#d22</code></td><td>Error / destructive state</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--color-status-info</code></td><td><code>#26e</code></td><td>Informational state</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--color-brand</code></td><td><em>Required — set by app</em></td><td>Primary brand color</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>--color-accent</code></td><td><em>Required — set by app</em></td><td>Secondary accent color</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
  
    </div>
  </section>

</article>
